@database NotifyClass
@index "Classes.guide/Main"

@Node Main "RxMUI - Notify Class"


Notify class    @{"Index" link "Classes.guide/Main"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  You can't create object of Notify class in RxMUI, but it's
  attribute and methods can be used with any of its subclasses.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}AppMessage@{fg text}
  B GN
  Maybe unuseful, set when an icon is dropped on an object

  @{fg shine}ClassRevision@{fg text}
  N G
  Revision of the MUI class

  @{fg shine}ClassVersion@{fg text}
  N G
  Version of the MUI class

  @{fg shine}Helpline@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}Helpnode@{fg text}
  S ISG

  @{fg shine}ObjectID@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  An integer or a max 4 chars string

  @{fg shine}NoNotify@{fg text}
  B N

  @{fg shine}Parent@{fg text}
  S G
  The name of the Group/Family parent object.

  @{fg shine}RxMUIRevision@{fg text}
  N G
  Revision of the RxMUI external class

  @{fg shine}RxMUIVersion@{fg text}
  N G
  Version of the RxMUI external class

  @{fg shine}UserData@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  Free use integer attribute. Notified anytime it is set, not
  only when it changes!

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}NoNotifyset@{fg text}
  <attr>,<parm>

  @{fg shine}Set@{fg text}
  <attr>,<parm>

@EndNode

